      "updated": 1777333919168,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Rule of thumb: OSS v2 CRD substrate tops out where etcd does (~10–100k concurrent TaskActions per cluster).\nLeasor moves state off etcd into an in-memory sharded store, trading kubectl ergonomics for ~2–3 orders of magnitude headroom.",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Rule of thumb: OSS v2 CRD substrate tops out where etcd does (~10–100k concurrent TaskActions per cluster).\nLeasor moves state off etcd into an in-memory sharded store, trading kubectl ergonomics for ~2–3 orders of magnitude headroom.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "autoResize": true,
      "index": "brn"
    },
